ncluding Shopify webhooks), HTTP requests to any API, Google Sheets, Meta CAPI, TikTok Events API, email services, and hundreds of other apps. The visual scenario builder is more powerful than Zapier's for complex conditional logic and data transformation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Zapier better than Make.com for non-technical users?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Zapier is often considered simpler for very basic linear automations (A triggers B). Make.com's visual canvas is slightly steeper to learn initially but significantly more powerful for multi-step, branching, or iterative workflows. For Shopify store owners doing anything more complex than a single-step automation, Make.com's visual builder becomes an advantage once the learning curve is overcome."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I migrate from Zapier to Make.com?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"List all active Zaps and document what each does (trigger, actions, filters). Recreate each in Make.com as a scenario. Test with sample data before activating. Then deactivate the Zapier version. The process takes roughly 30–60 minutes per complex Zap. Simple single-action Zaps migrate in 5–10 minutes each. Once migrated, cancel your Zapier subscription from the billing settings."}}]},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://stackarchitect.xyz"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Tools","item":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/tools/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Make vs Zapier Cost Calculator","item":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/make-vs-zapier-cost-calculator/"}]}];

